#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:38
msgid ""
"``block.prevrandao`` is an alias for the ``block.difficulty`` opcode. Since "
"``block.difficulty`` is considered deprecated according to `EIP-4399 "
"<https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4399>`_ after \"The Merge\" (Paris hard "
"fork), we recommend using ``block.prevrandao``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:42
msgid ""
"``msg.data`` requires the usage of :func:`slice <slice>` to explicitly "
"extract a section of calldata. If the extracted section exceeds the bounds "
"of calldata, this will throw. You can check the size of ``msg.data`` using :"
"func:`len <len>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:47
msgid "The self Variable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:49
msgid ""
"``self`` is an environment variable used to reference a contract from within "
"itself. Along with the normal :ref:`address<address>` members, ``self`` "
"allows you to read and write to state variables and to call private "
"functions within the contract."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:54
msgid "``self``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:54
msgid "Current contract's address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:55
msgid "``self.balance``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:55
msgid "Current contract's balance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:59
msgid "Accessing State Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:61
msgid ""
"``self`` is used to access a contract's :ref:`state variables<structure-"
"state-variables>`, as shown in the following example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:63
msgid ""
"state_var: uint256\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def set_var(value: uint256) -> bool:\n"
"    self.state_var = value\n"
"    return True\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"@view\n"
"def get_var() -> uint256:\n"
"    return self.state_var"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:79
msgid "Calling Internal Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:81
msgid ""
"``self`` is also used to call :ref:`internal functions<structure-functions-"
"internal>` within a contract:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:83
msgid ""
"@internal\n"
"def _times_two(amount: uint256) -> uint256:\n"
"    return amount * 2\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def calculate(amount: uint256) -> uint256:\n"
"    return self._times_two(amount)"
msgstr ""
"@internal\n"
"def _times_two(amount: uint256) -> uint256:\n"
"    return amount * 2\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def calculate(amount: uint256) -> uint256:\n"
"    return self._times_two(amount)"

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:96
msgid "Custom Constants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:98
msgid ""
"Custom constants can be defined at a global level in Vyper. To define a "
"constant, make use of the ``constant`` keyword."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../constants-and-vars.rst:100
msgid ""
"TOTAL_SUPPLY: constant(uint256) = 10000000\n"
"total_supply: public(uint256)\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__():\n"
"    self.total_supply = TOTAL_SUPPLY"
msgstr ""
